title: Ryder Cup stars meet with fans in Rome ahead of competition
description: The stars of this year's Ryder Cup walked down Rome's famous Spanish Steps on Wednesday - days before teeing off in the famous golfing competition.

title: Ex-Spain boss to be investigated as part of Rubiales 'kissgate' probe
description: Spain's Women's World Cup winning ex-manager Jorge Vilda is to be investigated as part of the Luis Rubiales "kissgate" probe.

title: Police arrest man in Dover the day after woman found dead on beach near Calais
description: British police have arrested a Sudanese man following the discovery of a migrant's body on Sangatte beach near Calais on Tuesday morning.

title: Why is Ukraine so successful in attacking key Russian military facilities?
description: Military analyst Sean Bell, along with other Sky experts, has been answering readers' most pressing questions daily about the war in Ukraine.

title: How often do you think about the Roman Empire? Expert has thoughts on the new TikTok trend
description: An expert has offered insight into why so many men, according to a highly popular TikTok trend, are obsessed with the Roman Empire.

title: Iran 'launches satellite into space' amid Western fears over nuclear threat
description: Iran claims to have successfully launched a third military satellite into orbit.

title: Antarctic winter sea ice hits 'extreme' low – smashing record set in 1986
description: Winter sea ice has reached an "extreme" record low in Antarctica - raising fears about the impact of climate change on the region and how it could have consequences for the rest of the world.

title: Suspected cocaine shipment worth up to 157m euros seized after army raid on cargo vessel
description: Customs officers in Ireland have sized 2,253kg of suspected cocaine - which could be worth 157 million euros (£136m).

title: 'Irresponsible' ads for Turkish cosmetic surgery tourism banned
description: Adverts promoting surgery at three cosmetic clinics in Turkey have been banned in the UK for "trivialising" the decision to go under the knife abroad.

title: North Korea plans to deport US soldier who crossed border via demilitarised zone
description: North Korea has said it plans to deport a US soldier who crossed the border with South Korea earlier this year.

title: Six young activists say 32 governments violated their rights in David and Goliath climate court case
description: Six young people from Portugal have taken 32 European governments to court, arguing their failure to act fast enough on climate change violates their human rights.

title: Joe Biden's dog bites another Secret Service agent
description: Joe Biden's dog has bitten yet another member of the US Secret Service - the 11th time such an incident has happened.

title: Thousands flee along 100 miles of winding road to Armenia after military offensive
description: More than 47,000 people have left Nagorno-Karabakh after Azerbaijan launched a military offensive to reclaim control of the disputed territory.

title: Man wrongfully convicted of rape, kidnapping and robbery freed after almost 30 years
description: A US man who spent nearly 30 years in prison for kidnapping, rape and robbery has been declared innocent and freed.

title: Costa Rica to declare state of emergency over increase in migrant numbers
description: Officials in Costa Rica will declare a state of emergency due to a sharp rise in the number of migrants passing through the country.

title: Shakira charged with 6.7m euro tax fraud
description: Shakira has been charged with tax evasion for the second time in Spain after she was accused of defrauding the state of 6.7m euros (about £5.8m).

title: Football star threatens to sue his own club
description: Napoli striker Victor Osimhen has threatened to take his own club to court over a video on TikTok appearing to mock him for missing a penalty.

title: Hollywood writers agree to end five-month strike after new studio deal
description: Hollywood film and TV writers are going back to work after nearly 150 days on strike in a dispute over pay, staffing levels and the emergence of artificial intelligence (AI).
